Combinational circuit design flow is a five-step process.

Step 1: System Specification
In this step, the designer identifies the number of input and output variables required. The user may not always specify these details, so the designer must determine the optimal number of inputs and outputs. Additionally, invalid conditionsâ€”cases where certain inputs or outputs cannot occurâ€”must be identified.

Step 2: Generating the Truth Table
The next step involves generating the truth table based on the input variables. For any system with 
